"Black in color and impenetrable to light.  This is a wheat beer?  A quarter inch of beige head is visible and leaves Brussels lacing.  I smell dark wheat and some toffee notes.  I taste toffee and dark wheat.  The body is moderately carbonated and creamy."
"Pours a black color.  1/4 inch head of an off-tan color.  Good retention and decent lacing.  Smells of alcohol, sweet malt, dark citrus, hint of tea, hint of yeast, and wheat.  Fits the style of an American Dark Wheat Ale.  Mouth feel is sharp and crisp, with an average carbonation level.  There is also a noticeable dryness.  Tastes of alcohol, sweet malt, wheat, hint of tea, hint of yeast, hint of hop, and a hint of roasted malt.  Overall, dominated by the roast, wheat, and dryness."
