"Overall / Drinkability:  Well, this is the first time I've had an American Dark Wheat Ale - and from what I see of the BA description of this style, this beer doesn't quite fit.  It does however, come across as a stout and if I look at it that way - a stout with a wheat base, it's pretty good.  I'm glad I got a six pack so I can explore this one a bit more.  I don't think I would want more than one a night, but it's still a good beer."
