"The alcohol was here but I could hardly detect it and it emerged as a nice waring sensation as I worked my way through this.The rings of lacing on the back of my pint glass was the icing on the cake as this beer felt wonderful from start to finish. As far as seasonal beers go, this one deserves to be put in anyone's rotation, especially as an alternate to the stronger and spicier offerings on the shelf this time of the year. A well-balanced beer that went down easily and is good enough to be enjoyed long after the presents are opened and the lights are taken down."
